text: I generally dislike when people are instructing others in how to have fun. I find this article to be pretentious. This guy just want to feel clever for playing obscure cards. Part of being a good deck builder is understanding that the community has already done that research and using that to your advantage.
People obsess way to much over having a unique deck, and how that supposedly defines you as a magic player
There's plenty of creative ground to be broken by mixing and matching different archetypes in unusual ways and /or with unexpected commanders.
EDHrec is a valuable tool in the process of building such a deck.
Exactly, it helps you build decks at pretty much every stage of your growth as a deck builder.
From your first deck where you don't know how many lands to run, to when you write articles about EDH.
